ion transcript to inspect is `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.security.enterprise:jakarta.security.enterprise-api:4.0.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T22-44-29-826560Z.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially the removal of the `IdentityStorePermission` test in `tests/src/jakarta.security.enterprise/jakarta.security.enterprise-api/4.0.0/.../Jakarta_security_enterprise_apiTest.java` and the metadata updates in `metadata/jakarta.security.enterprise/jakarta.security.enterprise-api/index.json`.\n2. Re-run the library checks on the preserved commit, at minimum `compileTestJava` and `test` for `jakarta.security.enterprise:jakarta.security.enterprise-api:4.0.0`, to confirm the later passing logs match the branch state.\n3. If that rerun is green, recreate or recover the PR from the preserved branch and treat the original human-intervention escalation as a failed automation-status/metrics update rather than a remaining javac failure."}}
